Cheers.

@onichols-pivotal 

> Strictly speaking, this PR actually shortens the feedback time by 2 hours. Before, all Linux tests ran, then all Windows tests ran. Now they run at the same time.

I disagree, currently the windows tests are not included in the default feedback loop and don't gate the release, therefor the time it takes to run windows is not additive in the current, its 0. The proposed change makes it part of the default feedback loop, which will now have a 2+ hour longer feedback time.
